🏗️ 1. Abstract Classes

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔹 What is an Abstract Class?

```text id="abstract_class_def"
An abstract class is a class that cannot be instantiated directly and serves as a blueprint for other classes.
```

---

🎯 Why Use Abstract Classes?

✔ Enforce implementation rules
✔ Improve code consistency
✔ Provide common structure
✔ Support large-scale applications

---

🔧 Real-Life Example

```text id="vehicle_example"
Vehicle

    ↑

Car
Bike
Truck
```

Every vehicle should have:

✔ start()

✔ stop()

But implementation may differ.

---

📥 Import ABC Module

Python provides the `abc` module.

---

💻 Example

```python id="abc_import"
from abc import ABC, abstractmethod
```

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔹 Creating an Abstract Class

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

💻 Example

```python id="abstract_class_example"
from abc import ABC, abstractmethod

class Vehicle(ABC):

    @abstractmethod
    def start(self):
        pass
```

---

⚠️ Important

Abstract classes cannot be instantiated.

---

❌ Example

```python id="abstract_error"
vehicle = Vehicle()
```

---

▶️ Output

```text id="abstract_error_output"
TypeError:
Can't instantiate abstract class
```

---

🔹 Implementing Abstract Methods

---

💻 Example

```python id="implement_abstract"
from abc import ABC, abstractmethod

class Vehicle(ABC):

    @abstractmethod
    def start(self):
        pass

class Car(Vehicle):

    def start(self):
        print("Car Started")

car = Car()

car.start()
```

---

▶️ Output

```text id="implement_output"
Car Started
```

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🎯 Multiple Abstract Methods

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

💻 Example

```python id="multiple_abstract"
from abc import ABC, abstractmethod

class Shape(ABC):

    @abstractmethod
    def area(self):
        pass

    @abstractmethod
    def perimeter(self):
        pass
```

---

💻 Child Class

```python id="shape_example"
class Rectangle(Shape):

    def area(self):
        return 100

    def perimeter(self):
        return 40
```

---

📌 Benefits of Abstract Classes

✔ Standardized architecture

✔ Better maintainability

✔ Code reusability

✔ Stronger design principles

