🔧 Best Practices

✔ Use abstract classes for common interfaces
✔ Prefer generators over complex iterators
✔ Use iterators for large datasets
✔ Keep custom iterators simple
✔ Raise StopIteration correctly

---

⚠️ Common Mistakes

❌ Instantiating abstract classes
❌ Forgetting abstract method implementation
❌ Missing __next__()
❌ Infinite iterators accidentally
❌ Not handling StopIteration

---

🧠 Interview Answer (Simple)

> Abstract classes define a blueprint for subclasses and cannot be instantiated directly. Iterators are objects that produce values one at a time using the iterator protocol, making them memory-efficient for processing large datasets.

